Tailwind v4 uses `@import 'tailwindcss'` instead of the v3 `@tailwind` directives. Theme customization uses `@theme` blocks instead of `tailwind.config.js`. The `cn()` utility from `clsx` + `tailwind-merge` is essential for conditional classes in component libraries.

CSS Modules provide locally scoped class names with zero runtime overhead. They work in both Server and Client Components and are built into Next.js with no configuration.

```css
/* components/Button.module.css */
.button {
  padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
  border-radius: 0.375rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  transition: background-color 0.2s;
}

.primary {
  background-color: #3b82f6;
  color: white;
}

.primary:hover {
  background-color: #2563eb;
}

